# Generated by Cargo
# will have compiled files and executables
target

# Debug-export and deadlock-dump artifacts written by the client into
# `<repo>/debug/` and `<crate>/debug/`. Ignore the contents (not the
# directory itself) so audit progress — which lives in the same folder
# — can be re-included by the rule below. Git cannot un-ignore a file
# inside an excluded directory, hence the `debug/*` form over plain
# `debug`.
debug/*
**/debug/*

# Audit progress is tracked across sessions. The audit feature
# (crabomination_client::audit) writes a JSON list of verified card names
# to debug/audited_cards.json — keep it under version control so the
# team's verification state survives across machines.
!**/audited_cards.json

# These are backup files generated by rustfmt
**/*.rs.bk

# MSVC Windows builds of rustc generate these, which store debugging information
*.pdb

# Generated by cargo mutants
# Contains mutation testing data
**/mutants.out*/

# RustRover
#  JetBrains specific template is maintained in a separate JetBrains.gitignore that can
#  be found at https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/Global/JetBrains.gitignore
#  and can be added to the global gitignore or merged into this file.  For a more nuclear
#  option (not recommended) you can uncomment the following to ignore the entire idea folder.
#.idea/

# Card images are auto-downloaded from Scryfall on first run by
# `crabomination_client::scryfall::ensure_card_images`; tracking them just
# bloats the repo and goes stale when the catalog grows. Fonts stay tracked
# (they're not auto-fetched and the UI needs them at startup).
crabomination_client/assets/cards/

# Per-user Claude Code harness settings (allow-lists, hooks, etc.).
# Each contributor maintains their own.
.claude/settings.local.json

# Python bytecode cache from running scripts/*.py (audit_strixhaven2.py,
# verify_cards.py, etc.). Auto-generated by the interpreter; never tracked.
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
